createddate.description: Date the document was created. Please use createddatetime instead.

documentroute.description: Explains method by which the document was entered into the AthenaNet (INTERFACE (digital), FAX, etc.)

externalaccessionid.description: The external accession ID for this document. Format depends on the system the ID belongs to.

lastmodifieduser.description: The user who last modified this document.

actionnote.description: The most recent action note for a document

providerusername.description: The username of the provider associated with this lab result document.

internalaccessionid.description: The internal accession ID for this document. Format depends on the system the ID belongs to.

isconfidential.description: If true, this result document should not be shown to the patient.

interpretation.description: The practice entered interpretation of this result.

labresultid.description: The primary key for labresult class of documents

labresultloinc.description: Laboratory code that identifies the overall result.

lastmodifieddatetime.description: Date/time (ISO 8601) the document was last modified

analyteid.description: Athena ID for the given lab result observation/analyte

analytename.description: Name / description specific to this analyte

loinc.description: Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes ID, if available

units.description: Units for this analyte entry, if provided by the lab

analytedate.description: Date when this observation was recorded

description.description: General description of the lab result test

note.description: Additional note for this analyte, if applicable

abnormalflag.description: Status indicator of the measurement relative to normal (low, high, normal, abnormal)

abnormalhl7code.description: The HL7 code related to the abnormal flag.

abnormalhl7name.description: The HL7 description related to the abnormal flag.

valuestatus.description: DEPRECATED -- use "abnormalflag" instead. Status indicator of the measurement relative to normal (low, high, normal, abnormal)

referencerange.description: Reference range of values accepted as normal for this observation

resultstatus.description: The status of the result (e.g., "final", "preliminary", "corrected", etc.)

labresultstatus.description: The status of the underlying lab result

priority.description: Document priority, when available. 1 is high, 2 is normal. Some labs use other numbers or characters that are lab-specific.

alarmdays.description: The number days, weeks, months, or year until a lab result document will go into followup after being sent to the portal.

documenttypeid.description: The ID of the description for this document

appointmentid.description: The appointment ID for this document

assignedto.description: Person the document is assigned to

createduser.description: The user who created this document.

lastmodifieddate.description: Date/time (ISO 8601) the document was last modified

encounterdate.description: Date of the encounter associated with this document

facilityid.description: The ID of the clinical provider associated with this clinical document. Clinical providers are a master list of providers throughout the country. These include providers as well as radiology centers, labs and pharmacies.

internalnote.description: The 'Internal Note' attached to this document

patientnote.description: A note about this lab result for the patient. This may or may not have been sent to the patient.

tietoorderid.description: Order ID of the order this document is tied to, if any
